      "writtenOn": "2019-10-31T20:39:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "the service is called resultdb as opposed to testResultDb or testResults because ChromeOS already requested to be able to fetch build artifacts, another result of a CI system. The Invocations/Inclusions/etc infra is reusable for that goal. Hence ResultSink.\n\nI didn\u0027t find a better word than \"result\" for various user-level results from a CI system. We didn\u0027t launch yet, but otherwise renaming it again would be disruptive.\n\nlarge amount of data is what we target. there is a lot of test results. What is the concern?",
      "parentUuid": "e25f86ba_0014adea",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 22,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 22,
        "endChar": 13
      },
      "revId": "233fb6e2f3c388e7f180e78d62f6532a9a709dbe",
