      "writtenOn": "2019-11-04T21:23:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "@nodir I believe other ResultDB products will also use LUCI_CONTEXT in the future, is that correct?\n\n@iannucci the original design doc called for a nested hierarchy, so that you we\u0027d have a top-level struct called \"resultdb\" and then each of its fields would be another struct, in this case \"resultdb.sink\". Is it possible to do something like this with LUCI_CONTEXT?\n\nIf that\u0027s not possible then I vote we consolidate all LUCI_CONTEXT values from ResultDB under one top-level struct, so that what is currently \"Port\" would be named \"SinkPort\" and referred to as \"resultdb.SinkPort\".",
      "parentUuid": "efacb0a3_982ae96e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 22,
        "startChar": 3,
