      "writtenOn": "2019-11-05T00:39:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e @nodir I believe other ResultDB products will also use LUCI_CONTEXT in the future, is that correct?\n\u003e \n\u003e @iannucci the original design doc called for a nested hierarchy, so that you we\u0027d have a top-level struct called \"resultdb\" and then each of its fields would be another struct, in this case \"resultdb.sink\". Is it possible to do something like this with LUCI_CONTEXT?\n\nYou could name the keys \"a.b\", but a given key contains arbitrary JSON; if you want it to have another nested key, then LUCI_CONTEXT doesn\u0027t really care.\n\n\u003e \n\u003e If that\u0027s not possible then I vote we consolidate all LUCI_CONTEXT values from ResultDB under one top-level struct, so that what is currently \"Port\" would be named \"SinkPort\" and referred to as \"resultdb.SinkPort\".",
      "parentUuid": "9601f51d_57034753",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 22,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 22,
        "endChar": 13
      },
